title: Matchsafe, "Cigar Butt", late 19th century
markings: On bezel: 2 eagle heads, 664. On attached link: Illegible diamond shaped stamp, DEPOSE.
provenance: Collection of Carol B. Brener and Stephen W. Brener
creditline: Gift of Stephen W. Brener and Carol B. Brener
description: In the form of a short cigar butt, with leaves defined on realistically cast body in gold, the tip with ashes in silver metal. Tip hinged at side and opens as lid. Tip also likely intended as striker.
